title: Tummy Tracker: Build a Healthier Lifestyle!
description: A web app that helps users plan and shop for food safely by tracking individual and group dietary needs, allergies, medical conditions, medications, and age-specific requirements. It scans ingredients for real-time suitability analysis, provides personalized and group feedback with health impact warnings, and offers a dashboard with long-term visualizations of ingredient consumption and health trends.

title: InterPrep: Track and refine your technical interview practice!
description: A web app that helps users prepare for technical interviews by combining coding practice with communication training. It presents LeetCode-style questions, records and transcribes spoken explanations, and evaluates them using a structured rubric. Users receive personalized feedback on clarity, structure, and technical understanding, plus recommended practice questions filtered by difficulty, algorithm type, problem-solving pattern, or company relevance.

title: Whisper Web
description: A user-friendly web interface that leverages OpenAI's Whisper (an automatic speech recognition model) to transcribe speech from both uploaded audio/video files and directly recorded microphone input. It processes diverse media formats, extracts audio from videos when necessary, and provides accurate text transcriptions with an option for users to preview their recordings before transcription.

title: Butterfly Species Classification Using Transfer Learning with ResNet50
description: Achieved a 69.3% training and 72.4% validation accuracy by training a custom convolutional neural network (SimpleButterflyCNN) model to classify 9,000+ butterfly images across 75 species. Applied transfer learning with the ResNet50, significantly improving classification results to a 96.7% training and 91.8% validation accuracy (Precision: 0.92, Recall: 0.91, F1-score: 0.91, Support: 1300), amplifying generalization accuracy.
technologies: Python, NumPy, Pandas, PyTorch, Torchvision, Pillow, TQDM, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn

title: Random Forest Analysis of Health and Poverty Dynamics in the U.S. (2015-2025)
description: Synthesized and cleaned 35,000+ multi-source US health, poverty and population records (Google PDFM, County Health Rankings) with complex joins, data mappings, and missing data remediation. Built and evaluated multi-target Random Forest regression models (scikit-learn), using imputation and feature importance to identify smoking rates as the top predictor of poor mental & physical health days.
technologies: Python, Jupyter Notebooks, NumPy, Pandas, Scikit-learn, Matplotlib, Seaborn, DuckDB

title: Specialty Candy Shop: Data-Driven Plan TO Prevent Inventory Shortages
description: Integrated SQL Server data tables spanning logistics, sales, targets, and product information to find optimization strategies and critical operational issues. Designed a range-based inventory strategy using Holt-Winters exponential smoothing (statsmodels) to forecast demand with fixed seasonality, guiding long-term planning on inventory and capacity decisions to a 5-year operational lead time.

title: AlgeBlitz
description: A maths-based mobile app to gamify learning -- from algebraic fundamentals, to advanced mathematical theory, and practical applications. Designed and prototyped app screens in Figma for diverse use cases, and implemented frontend components. Created and automated UI, heartbeat, unit, and integration tests, achieving a code coverage of 48.48%.

title: CareerCheer
description: Participated in CTP Hacks 2025. CareerCheer is a simple, user-friendly mobile app designed to help students track their internship and job hunting progress through the application stages.

title: MANJU
description: A cross-functional food-ordering, food delivery, customer complaint system, inventory tracker, and payroll management all-in-one mobile app. It connects chefs, delivery personnel, food importers, administrators, and customers. Some features include a GUI displaying a menu of dishes and reviews, personalized top dish selections, a performance evaluation system for chefs and delivery personnel, customer dining options (in-store, pickup, or delivery), ingredient inventory tracking for chefs, resupply access for food importers, and an employee payroll and management system.

title: CSV Scrambler
description: A Python command-line tool with multiple modes and options to scramble "clean" CSV files into "dirty" or non-standardized CSVs. This tool can help with data cleaning & formatting practice.
